thread.title: Several incumbents win re-election

author: Posted by WAFB Staff
title: Several incumbents win re-election
text:
BATON ROUGE, LA (WAFB) - To get the latest election results, click here .
John Kennedy was re-elected as Louisiana state treasurer.
Mike Strain was also re-elected as Louisiana commissioner of agriculture.
Two incumbent sheriffs held onto their seats, as Livingston Parish Sheriff Jason Ard and West Baton Rouge Parish Sheriff Mike Cazes were both re-elected.
Tom Schedler was re-elected as Louisiana secretary of state and Jim Donelon was re-elected as commissioner of insurance.
